{
  "stem": "13600.3",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 95,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Let's say if when the Germans were going forward and conquering this city, and that city, you used to say, after a long and bitter struggle, the city was evacuated.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 95,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "This was the language.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 95,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So I knew what had happened.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 96,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And let's say when Stalingrad, which was the turning point, Stalingrad, that was, let's see, January '43 was the turning point in the Second World War, where the Germans-- I at that time, made up my mind, I, myself-- the Germans have lost the war.",
      "word_count": 45
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 96,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It was the first time that the whole army was surrounded, German army defeated.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 96,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And as a matter of fact, from that time, the Russians started going forward all the time.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 96,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "That was the last piece of land that the Germans reached, was this.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 96,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "From then on--",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 97,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It was back the other way.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 98,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Back the other way.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 99,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 99,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I somehow had a hope I would survive.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 99,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I don't-- I couldn't visualize otherwise.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 99,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Otherwise I wouldn't have survived, perhaps.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 100,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 101,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh yes.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 102,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 102,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "From 1943, they-- they said they have taken 110, 120,000 Germans-- [PAUSES FOR 8 SECONDS] how do you say?",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 102,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And also I remember the Russian word, [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 102,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They have taken them in [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] captivity.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 102,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Would that be correct word?",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 102,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "With the field marshal.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 102,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "This was the beginning of the end of the Germans, of the Nazi Germany.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 103,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "As far as I remember, the uprising in Warsaw ghetto, I remember in '43.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 104,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 105,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 105,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They usually-- they usually tried to hide the Jewish part of it, for obvious reason.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 105,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The Nazis presented their struggle-- their war as a war against Jews.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 105,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "The Russians, the communists, presented their struggle as a struggle for freedom, for democracy.",
      "word_count": 14
    }
  ],
